Finance Minister János Veres and Marta Gajecka, Vice-President of the European Investment Bank (EIB), signed three credit agreements worth EUR 400 million on Friday in Budapest. The money will be channelled into education, transport and environmental infrastructure and the energy industry.
In 2006, the European Investment Bank (EIB) approved a EUR 300 million framework for the financing of transport and environmental projects implemented with grants from the Cohesion Fund. The EUR 200 million loan agreement has already been signed in the past, the current agreement deals with the use of EUR 200 million.
