Its publication is in line with the principles of Eurostat and the European Central Bank (ECB), which aim to make local and quality comparisons with US products through the provision of the data.
The forecast for the indicator can be prepared in advance by using the same approach as for the harmonised consumer price index, but at the same time by using various other statistical modelling methods to estimate the information not available at the time of calculation.
However, the Spanish Statistical Office (INE) warned that the indicator identified in advance would only serve as a benchmark and therefore would not have to be consistent with the final result announced next 14 December.
The Consumer Price Index (IPI) will remain at a relatively high level
According to the Deputy Head of Government and the Minister for Economic Affairs and Finance Pedro Solbes, the increase in the VPI was a temporary development in November , while at the same time ensuring that the price index would remain at a relatively high level in the coming months.
Nevertheless , Solbes found in the halls of the Congress building that even if the current figure is not good , the inflation difference of Spain to the other members of the Monetary Union has remained more or less the same in recent years.
He also stated that there were fewer surprises in November than in the previous month, where the government did not expect such a high increase.
We expected a value of around 4% , the Minister of Economic Affairs and Finance announced in view of the forecast published today.
