Which insurance is best for me?
The motor vehicle insurance covering a possible damage caused by the driver includes a high cost, the amount of which again depends on different factors, such as age, gender, the date of issue of the driver's licence, family status, the type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, you have to be clear about what we're dealing with here.
Auto insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract, which shall determine that the company receives the insurance premium agreed upon and shall, in return, be obliged to submit the corresponding sum of compensation in the event of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of insurance consisting of several factors, such as age, gender, date of issue of the licence, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contributions are also made in the event of a higher risk of accidents.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to make fewer contributions because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate due to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since, according to the statistical values and thus also according to the company's conviction, they tend to be less accidents than single persons.
The benefits to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In drawing up the premium, insurance must take into account a whole range of points.
For this reason, the driver also needs to study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best meets his personal needs.
We are now listing the most important points to consider when choosing insurance in order not only to be able to make a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
The under 25-year-olds face numerous obstacles when choosing a low-priced insurance policy, such as low driving practices and young driving licences.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance policy to complete full insurance, there are nevertheless cheaper alternatives.
The careful drivers can choose a full-time checkout with self-participation, so that the benefits of full-time insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract includes that the customer must pay part of the amount resulting from the damage himself.
The amount is determined prior to the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher than the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, Spain's main representative at First Europe, an intermediary for online insurance.
Another option is the extended insurance, which assures the customer against external damage, but not against the damage caused on his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's a advice.
When you are under 25 years of age, it is in your hand to reduce insurance costs; so your credit will increase by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate for the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase in the rates indicated.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a lucrative year behind it, it may be possible to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. Reason for this is the fact that the accident rate decreases with increasing driving practice.
Thus, it is most appropriate to opt for full-time insurance with self-share.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving , explains the Spanish president of the European company and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been eliminated.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out full insurance; of course, only if it allows the financial situation of the person concerned.
On the part of insurers, couples with children are considered to be customers with the lowest accident rate, and therefore their contributions are also low.
In this case, full insurance with self-employment (with an amount of EUR 300) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy is recommended, which only applies to the third vehicle year.
They are generally more relaxed and have a greater purchasing power that allows them to make a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is possible to take out full-time insurance with self-employment (for an amount of 150 euros) or an extended insurance which only applies to a sufficiently high credit.
In the end, one must note that car insurance is very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it involves high costs, which require a thorough selection that corresponds to our personal situation.
